Parliament, Wednesday 20 May 2020 - The National Assembly will tomorrow convene its Programme Committee meeting to plan for the business of House.
	
	Amongst issues to be considered are the committee reports, virtual plenaries of the House, Bills before the House and the upcoming programme of the National Assembly.
	
	Details of the virtual meeting: 
	
	Date: Thursday, 21 May 2020 Time: 08:30 am 
	The meeting will take place via online video platform. 
	
	Members of the media who would like to be part of the meeting to observe, may forward their cellphone numbers to Mlindi Mpindi on email mmpindi@parliament.gov.za for inclusion in the Parliamentary Communications Services WhatsApp Group, where login details will be shared. Journalists are urged to forward the request using their official email addresses (no private emails).
	
	Members of the public may follow the committee sitting live on Parliament TV (DSTV Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA 
